// Cluster 11 — NEW commercial slicer repair pillar.
// Same template family as kettle-repair pillar (CommercialHero + 10 sections + 4 schemas).
// $120 commercial diagnostic. Em-dash budget: ≤2 visible body. NO C-38, NO C-20 (mechanical
// equipment, not refrigeration/HVAC). BHGS #A49573 + EPA 608 #1346255700410.
//
// Brand factual: Hobart (ITW Food Equipment), Globe (Edgecraft, independent),
// Bizerba (independent German), Berkel (US Foods Equipment heritage 1898).
// Health Department sanitization angle + OSHA blade-guard/safety-interlock angle.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CommercialHero from '../../components/CommercialHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/slicer-repair/";

const title = "Commercial Meat Slicer Repair LA | Hobart HS, Globe, Bizerba, Berkel — OSHA + Health Dept Compliant";
const description = "Commercial meat slicer repair across SoCal. Hobart HS, Globe, Bizerba, Berkel. OSHA blade guard service, Health Dept sanitization compliance. $120 dx.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do you service Hobart, Globe, Bizerba, and Berkel slicers?",
    a: "Yes. Hobart (ITW Food Equipment) HS-series gravity-feed slicers are the dominant US market and the bulk of our service volume. Globe (Edgecraft, independent) is common in mid-volume delis. Bizerba (German independent) appears in upscale charcuterie operations and butcher shops. Berkel (US Foods Equipment, heritage 1898) is the heritage brand still in service in many longstanding LA delis. We have brand-specific knowledge across all four."
  },
  {
    q: "My slicer blade has lost its edge. Can you sharpen it on-site?",
    a: "Yes. On-site honing for routine edge maintenance is standard. Full blade sharpening with built-in sharpener service runs $140 to $260. Blade replacement (when sharpening is no longer viable) runs $380 to $720 depending on blade size and brand. We use OEM blades; aftermarket blades are not recommended for safety and Health Department inspection reasons."
  },
  {
    q: "What does OSHA require for slicer safety?",
    a: "OSHA mandates blade guards in place during operation, safety interlocks that stop the blade when guards are removed, and proper training documentation for slicer operators. We service blade guards (replacement when bent or damaged), safety interlocks (the most common compliance failure point), and provide service documentation that operators can retain for OSHA inspection records. A slicer running without functional safety interlocks is an OSHA citation waiting to happen."
  },
  {
    q: "Health Department sanitization for slicers: what's required?",
    a: "LA County Health Department requires daily sanitization (not just cleaning) of slicers used for ready-to-eat foods. The blade, blade guard, food chute, food carriage, and slicer base all require breakdown for proper sanitization. NSF-listed slicer parts are required; we install only NSF-listed OEM replacement parts so your slicer remains Health Dept inspection-ready."
  },
  {
    q: "Why do slicer motors burn out?",
    a: "Three causes, in order of frequency: (1) bearing wear from inadequate lubrication during sharpening service, (2) overload trip from cutting frozen or partially frozen products (slicer motors aren't rated for frozen), (3) age (year 8 to 12 typical service life on Hobart HS, longer on Bizerba premium). We diagnose with multimeter and bearing inspection; replacement motor runs $580 to $980 depending on slicer size and brand."
  },
  {
    q: "What does commercial slicer repair cost in LA?",
    a: "$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Common repairs: blade sharpener service $140 to $260, blade replacement $380 to $720, safety interlock replacement $260 to $440, blade guard replacement $220 to $380, motor replacement $580 to $980, sharpener stone replacement $140 to $240, drive belt $180 to $320, food carriage rebuild $440 to $720. Multi-component repair on aged units $890 to $1,800."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. Hobart, Globe, Bizerba, and Berkel component warranties (where applicable) processed separately through manufacturer authorized networks. BHGS #A49573 and BBB A+. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410."
  }
];

