<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Slicer service</p>
    <h2>Commercial slicer service for delis, butcher shops, charcuterie, and restaurant operations.</h2>

    <p>Commercial meat slicers are the workhorses of delis, butcher shops, charcuterie programs, sandwich operations, and any kitchen processing volume cold cuts, cheeses, or roasts. Slicers also carry the heaviest combined OSHA safety and Health Department sanitization compliance burden of any small commercial kitchen appliance. We service commercial slicers across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties.</p>

    <p><strong>Hobart HS-series gravity-feed slicers</strong> (ITW Food Equipment) dominate the US market and the bulk of our service volume. <strong>Globe slicers</strong> (Edgecraft, independent) are common in mid-volume delis and sandwich operations. <strong>Bizerba</strong> (German independent) appears in upscale charcuterie operations, premium butcher shops, and Italian deli operations across LA. <strong>Berkel</strong> (US Foods Equipment, heritage 1898) is the heritage brand still in service in many longstanding LA delis; some Berkel units in LA service have been running since the 1970s with periodic component replacement.</p>

    <p>Our service scope covers blade sharpening (built-in sharpener service or full blade sharpening), blade replacement, safety interlock service (the most common OSHA compliance failure point), blade guard replacement, motor replacement, sharpener stone, drive belt, food carriage rebuild, and complete sanitization-compliant component service. NSF-listed OEM parts only.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573 license. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/licensed/">License verifiable.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Failure modes</p>
    <h2>Typical commercial slicer failures, in order of frequency.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Slicer service mix reflects the combination of mechanical wear (blade, motor, drive belt) and compliance-driven service items (safety interlocks, blade guards, sharpener stones).</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Blade dulling.</strong> Routine maintenance item. On-site honing every 30 to 90 days depending on volume; full sharpening with built-in sharpener service $140 to $260; blade replacement when sharpening is no longer viable $380 to $720.</li>
      <li><strong>Safety interlock failure.</strong> Year 5 to 9 typical. The most common OSHA compliance failure point. Slicer must stop blade when guard is removed; failed interlock means blade keeps spinning, which is an OSHA citation. $260 to $440 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Sharpener stone wear.</strong> Built-in sharpener stones lose abrasive surface over time. Replacement $140 to $240.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive belt wear.</strong> Slicer drive belt loses tension or shows cracking. Year 4 to 7 typical. $180 to $320.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor bearing wear.</strong> Year 8 to 12 typical on Hobart HS, longer on Bizerba premium. Causes: inadequate lubrication during sharpening service, overload trip from cutting frozen products. Replacement $580 to $980.</li>
      <li><strong>Blade guard damage.</strong> Bent or damaged blade guards from operator handling or sanitization breakdown. Replacement $220 to $380. OSHA-required.</li>
      <li><strong>Food carriage wear.</strong> The carriage tray that holds product against the blade develops slop or bearing wear. Rebuild $440 to $720.</li>
      <li><strong>Health Department sanitization-driven repairs.</strong> NSF-listed parts that have failed inspection. Replace with NSF-listed OEM only.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 BRANDS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Brand notes</p>
    <h2>What we see by brand on slicer service calls.</h2>

    <p><strong>Hobart (ITW Food Equipment).</strong> HS-series gravity-feed slicers (HS6, HS7, HS8, HS9 by blade size). Dominant US market. Standard service items: blade, sharpener stone, safety interlock, drive belt, motor. Parts via Hobart authorized distributor (5 to 7 day standard ship for less common items). Hobart's reputation for reliability is earned; year 12+ HS units still in service with proper maintenance.</p>

    <p><strong>Globe (Edgecraft, independent).</strong> Mid-volume delis and sandwich operations. Less expensive than Hobart, simpler architecture, fully serviceable. Common service: blade, sharpener, motor.</p>

    <p><strong>Bizerba (independent German).</strong> Premium charcuterie operations, upscale butcher shops, Italian deli operations. Higher precision, premium components, longer service life. Bizerba blade quality is exceptional; sharpening intervals can be longer. Parts via Bizerba US distribution (5 to 10 day ship on premium components).</p>

    <p><strong>Berkel (US Foods Equipment, heritage 1898).</strong> Heritage brand. Some Berkel units in LA service have been running since the 1970s with periodic component replacement. Modern Berkel parts available; vintage unit parts sometimes require aftermarket cross-reference. We service both modern and vintage Berkel.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five slicer service calls from the past year. Brand and model context, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Deli in Beverly Hills · Hobart HS8 (10 years)</h3>
        <p>Safety interlock failure flagged during health inspection (blade kept spinning briefly after guard removal). Replaced safety interlock plus serviced sharpener stone (overdue). Health Department received documentation same day; reinspection passed. Total: $480.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Italian charcuterie in West Hollywood · Bizerba SE12 (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Motor overload trip; operator had been slicing partially frozen prosciutto. Replaced motor bearing (early-stage wear, premium Bizerba spec). Educated operator on temperature requirements. Total: $740.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Sandwich shop in Pasadena · Globe G14 (6 years)</h3>
        <p>Blade dulling causing operator strain plus sharpener stone worn smooth. Full sharpening service plus stone replacement. Total: $360.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Butcher shop in Long Beach · Berkel 919 (modern, 4 years)</h3>
        <p>Drive belt cracking, slipping under load. Replaced drive belt plus realigned drive sheave. Total: $260.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Heritage deli in Los Angeles · Berkel vintage 1970s rebuild (50+ years)</h3>
        <p>Multi-component refurbishment: blade guard replacement (original was bent), safety interlock retrofit (original interlock no longer compliant), sharpener stone replacement, motor bearing service. Modern Berkel parts cross-referenced for several items. Total: $1,640. Owner happy to keep the original cabinet running.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
